serviceOrganisation.name: Australian Electoral Commission
serviceOrganisation.description: The role of the Australian Electoral Commission is to deliver the franchise: that is, an Australian citizen's right to vote, as established by the Commonwealth Electoral Act 1918.

serviceDimensions.name: Find My Electorate
serviceDimensions.description: Use this search to find which electorate you live in, see who your local Member is, find your nearest polling place on Election Day and look at a profile and Map of your electorate. A search will bring up a link to your local federal electorate; click on the 'more information' link to find your local member and his party.
